                <note rend="inline" type="source">123C853/6b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Commission to Negotiate Peace</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-04-23T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 23, 1919, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1701. Crane took oath today. Understand he will be commissioned in Paris. Letter
                    of credence will be prepared here and <pb facs="0171" n="86" xml:id="pg_86"/>
                    brought over by him for signature. Telegraph as soon as commission is signed so
                    passport as Minister may be issued.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
